<DOC><DOCNO> AP880308-0014 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-88 0058EST</FILEID><FIRST>r p BC-RhodeIslandAt-A-Glance     03-08 0207</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Rhode Island At-A-Glance,220</SECOND><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here, at a glance, are the methods for pickingdelegates from Rhode Island to attend the 1988 Democratic andRepublican national conventions this summer.</TEXT><HEAD>DEMOCRATS</HEAD><TEXT>   Method: Primary   Date: Tuesday, March 8   Candidates filed: Bruce Babbitt, Michael Dukakis, RichardGephardt, Albert Gore, Gary Hart, Jesse Jackson, Paul Simon   Pledged delegates: 22   Super delegates: 4   Total: 26   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, March 8   Selection of delegates: Tuesday, March 8 and Monday, June 13   Rhode Island's 14 pledged delegates to the Democratic NationalConvention from congressional districts will be chosen in adirect-election primary on March 8.   The rest of the state's eight pledged nationa conventiondelegates will be allocated among presidential candidates inproportion to the results of the primary.</TEXT><HEAD>REPUBLICANS</HEAD><TEXT>   Method: Primary   Date: Tuesday, March 8   Candidates filed: George Bush, Bob Dole, Jack Kemp, PatRobertson, Pete du Pont, Alexander Haig   Delegates: 21   Delegates allocated: Tuesday, March 8   Selection of delegates: Tuesday, March 8   Rhode Island Republicans elect their national conventiondelegates directly from the March 8 primary ballot. Delegates areallocated among presidential candidates in proportion to thestatewide vote.   A presidential candidate must receive at least 20 percent of thevote to qualify for any delegates.</TEXT></DOC>